text:
former u.s. national security adviser michael flynn admitted on friday that he asked russia to delay a u.n. vote seen as damaging to israel, but diplomats said it was not the only country he and presidential adviser jared kushner lobbied.

in the hours before the vote by the 15-member united nations security council on dec. 23, flynn also phoned the u.n. missions of uruguay and malaysia, and kushner spoke with kim darroch, the british ambassador to the united states, according to diplomats familiar with the conversations, who spoke on condition of anonymity.

the lobbying took place before republican president donald trump, who was known for his pro-israel campaign rhetoric, took office on jan. 20. it failed, with the security council adopting a resolution demanding an end to israeli settlement building on land palestinians want for an independent state. the vote was 14 in favor and one abstention by the united states.

the efforts made on israel's behalf capped several days of unusual diplomacy. in a surprise dec. 21 move, egypt had called for a vote the next day on the draft resolution, prompting both trump and israel to urge washington to veto the text.

a senior israeli official told reuters that israeli officials contacted trump's transition team at a "high level" to ask for help after failing to persuade democratic president barack obama's administration to veto the draft u.n. resolution.

according to court documents made public on friday, a member of trump's presidential transition team, later identified by sources as trump's son-in-law kushner, told flynn on dec. 22 to contact officials from foreign governments, including russia, to convince them to delay the vote or veto the resolution.

flynn spoke with then-russian ambassador to the united states sergei kislyak that day, and again the following day, according to the court documents.

michelle nichols
reuters

pre_proc_tweet:
former u.s. national security adviser michael flynn admitted on friday that he asked russia to delay a u.n. vote seen as damaging to israel, but diplomats said it was not the only country he and presidential adviser jared kushner lobbied.

in the hours before the vote by the 15-member united nations security council on dec. 23, flynn also phoned the u.n. missions of uruguay and malaysia, and kushner spoke with kim darroch, the british ambassador to the united states, according to diplomats familiar with the conversations, who spoke on condition of anonymity.

the lobbying took place before republican president donald trump, who was known for his pro-israel campaign rhetoric, took office on jan. 20. it failed, with the security council adopting a resolution demanding an end to israeli settlement building on land palestinians want for an independent state. the vote was 14 in favor and one abstention by the united states.

the effos made on israel's behalf capped several days of unusual diplomacy. in a surprise dec. 21 move, egypt had called for a vote the next day on the draft resolution, prompting both trump and israel to urge washington to veto the text.

a senior israeli official told reuters that israeli officials contacted trump's transition team at a "high level" to ask for help after failing to persuade democratic president barack obama's administration to veto the draft u.n. resolution.

according to cou documents made public on friday, a member of trump's presidential transition team, later identified by sources as trump's son-in-law kushner, told flynn on dec. 22 to contact officials from foreign governments, including russia, to convince them to delay the vote or veto the resolution.

flynn spoke with then-russian ambassador to the united states sergei kislyak that day, and again the following day, according to the cou documents.

michelle nichols
reuters

text:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

text:
christopher wylie, the whistleblower who exposed the widespread misuse of data by his former employer, cambridge analytica, has revealed how the company â€œweaponisedâ€ the fashion industry in the run up to the 2016 us election, which he claims helped donald trump get elected.

speaking at the annual bof voices festival in oxfordshire, wylie revealed for the first time a matrix based on data collected by the firm which he claims can show how usersâ€™ preferences for particular brands on social media platforms â€“ facebook, in particular â€“ were then used to help target these same users with pro-trump messaging. he compared the misuse of fashion-based data as one of the campaignâ€™s lesser reported â€œweapons of mass destructionâ€. - they [cambridge analytica] looked at actual people. how they engaged with certain brands was put into a funnel and helped build the algorithms, wylie explained. - when you look at personality traits, music and fashion are the most informative [tools] for predicting someoneâ€™s personality. a userâ€™s predilection for a particular label gives, he said, a very clear indication of what reports often call â€œpopulist political signallingâ€. cambridge analytica, which wasÂ shut down earlier this year following an investigation by the observer, was the political marketing firm headed by trumpâ€™s former key adviser, steve bannon, and owned by hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer. it also used user information obtained without authorisation in early 2014 â€“ including cultural preferences such as fashion and music â€“ to create a system that could single out voters in order to expose them to specific political advertising.

morwenna ferrier
the guardian

text:
misguided angel ~ the cowboy junkies
â€¢
"i said, "sister, don't you understand?
he's all i ever wanted in a man
i'm tired of sittin' around the t.v. every night
hoping i'm finding a mr. right."
â€¢
misguided angel hangin' over me
heart like gabriel, pure and white as ivory
soul like a lucifer
black and cold like a piece of lead
misguided angel, love you 'till i'm dead"
â€¢
for some strange reason, this song has been making a real comeback for me lately. i especially love the version featuring natalie merchant, along with margo timmons, on vocals. i believe the return of this song's presence, in this point of my life, has something to do with my misguided angel friend arden, but also, with you. for on my behalf, i've asked him to watch over you.
â€¢
note: somehow, i can't help but think, as with some of my favorite art (the pre-raphaelite work from the late 1800, early 1900's), the politically correct #metoo movement, would have a problem with this song, in retrospect. but then, al franklin was forced to walk the plank on his senatorship, and a misogynistic pig is still president. so fuck it anyway. as with the art of the pre-raphaelites, it's a beautiful, and timeless song.
â€¢

text:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

text:
hey insta! i need to post this. i am struggling with my mental health for years now. traumatised and what not. therefore my body showed how i felt and that wasn't good at all. (lost 30 kilo in one year!) so last year i was at my lowest point. it was hell! didn't feel human anymore. lonely as fuck. nobody seemed to understand what i was (and still) going through. that is ok tho! how can someone know? but i have been with people that wanted the worst for me. didn't care at all. this journey i did alone. i have cut those people out, started to be straight to myself. i couldn't run away in drugs and alcohol much longer! so i changed a lot. and dammit it feels so good now! sometimes the pain of being lonely creeps right back in. but i don't let it hang for long anymore, no way! this little dark monster is small now and i am stronger! i want to thank everyone that kept me down, judged me, left me hanging. cause you know what? i've learned so much from you guys. ;) and yes there were people in my life that gave me hope, love, the strength to go on, strangers they were! i keep you in my heartâ¤â¤â¤ forever! 
this year will be my new me that rocks the clouds!
and last but not least: just do it!
everyone that is struggling, you have my heart! if you need someone to talk pm me!
love and peace. pastelcore~~ #metoo #struggling #depression #positive #journey #youcandoit #lonely #justdoit #fitgirl #damsco #roffa #ptsd #ptss #cptss #weightloss #fromthebottomtothetop #pastecole #fitness #healthy #fuckeverynegativeperson #love #respect #selfworth #selfgrow #depressief #peace #pastelcore #hardcore #musicismylifesaver #pastelgore

text:
former u.s. national security adviser michael flynn admitted on friday that he asked russia to delay a u.n. vote seen as damaging to israel, but diplomats said it was not the only country he and presidential adviser jared kushner lobbied.

in the hours before the vote by the 15-member united nations security council on dec. 23, flynn also phoned the u.n. missions of uruguay and malaysia, and kushner spoke with kim darroch, the british ambassador to the united states, according to diplomats familiar with the conversations, who spoke on condition of anonymity.

the lobbying took place before republican president donald trump, who was known for his pro-israel campaign rhetoric, took office on jan. 20. it failed, with the security council adopting a resolution demanding an end to israeli settlement building on land palestinians want for an independent state. the vote was 14 in favor and one abstention by the united states.

the efforts made on israel's behalf capped several days of unusual diplomacy. in a surprise dec. 21 move, egypt had called for a vote the next day on the draft resolution, prompting both trump and israel to urge washington to veto the text.

a senior israeli official told reuters that israeli officials contacted trump's transition team at a "high level" to ask for help after failing to persuade democratic president barack obama's administration to veto the draft u.n. resolution.

according to court documents made public on friday, a member of trump's presidential transition team, later identified by sources as trump's son-in-law kushner, told flynn on dec. 22 to contact officials from foreign governments, including russia, to convince them to delay the vote or veto the resolution.

flynn spoke with then-russian ambassador to the united states sergei kislyak that day, and again the following day, according to the court documents.

michelle nichols
reuters

text:
richard's getting ready to celebrate his 5th month of his new life post lung transplant and stroke.  he's getting stronger every day.  we have a lot of medical bills that insurance does not cover; anti-rejection medications, anti-fungal medication ( $90/week) transportation costs to and from philadelphia, parking $12/day, stays at gift of life house $40/day, dr. co-pays of $35 per visit.  he's supposed to go to pulmonary rehab which will cost $35 each visit.  he needs this because he's fallen numerous times.  he must pay for his wheelchair,  hospital bed rental at home, cable for hospital stay of 3 1/2 months was $9/day.  we really need your support.  he will be taking these meds the rest of his life.  and we will have dr. appointments in #philly the rest of his life.  please donate to his fundraiser at: https://helphopelive.org/campaign/13723/  all donations are tax-deductible ( the link is in my bio) we chose this organization because donations will not count as income which won't affect his medicare benefits.  thank you for all of your positive thoughts, prayers and donations.  god bless!

text:
women & girls continue not to be believed, stereotypes, victimized, victim blamed, attacked, assaulted, & murdered. 
black women and girls since slavery have especially been hypersexualized, marginalized, silenced, & forgotten. 
rape culture, sexual assault, sexism, harassment, toxic masculinity, domestic abuse & misogyny are pervasive systemic issues that exist in every facet of society in homes, schools, work places, churches, & politics. 
aim to be an ally in verb form! believe survivors, challenge yourself, be willing to risk & sacrifice, lens your privilege, hold yourself & others accountable, know better & do better, stand with, empower, fight for &l beside women! 
#believesurvivors #timesup #metoo #womenmatter #blackgirlsmatter #blackwomenmatter

text:
former u.s. national security adviser michael flynn admitted on friday that he asked russia to delay a u.n. vote seen as damaging to israel, but diplomats said it was not the only country he and presidential adviser jared kushner lobbied.

in the hours before the vote by the 15-member united nations security council on dec. 23, flynn also phoned the u.n. missions of uruguay and malaysia, and kushner spoke with kim darroch, the british ambassador to the united states, according to diplomats familiar with the conversations, who spoke on condition of anonymity.

the lobbying took place before republican president donald trump, who was known for his pro-israel campaign rhetoric, took office on jan. 20. it failed, with the security council adopting a resolution demanding an end to israeli settlement building on land palestinians want for an independent state. the vote was 14 in favor and one abstention by the united states.

the efforts made on israel's behalf capped several days of unusual diplomacy. in a surprise dec. 21 move, egypt had called for a vote the next day on the draft resolution, prompting both trump and israel to urge washington to veto the text.

a senior israeli official told reuters that israeli officials contacted trump's transition team at a "high level" to ask for help after failing to persuade democratic president barack obama's administration to veto the draft u.n. resolution.

according to court documents made public on friday, a member of trump's presidential transition team, later identified by sources as trump's son-in-law kushner, told flynn on dec. 22 to contact officials from foreign governments, including russia, to convince them to delay the vote or veto the resolution.

flynn spoke with then-russian ambassador to the united states sergei kislyak that day, and again the following day, according to the court documents.

michelle nichols
reuters

text:
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text:
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn
